fastPathQOSAUTOVOIP.name: fastPathQOSAUTOVOIP

revisions.description: Added OUI based auto VoIP support.

fastPathQOSAUTOVOIP.description: The MIB definitions for Quality of Service - VoIP Flex package.

agentAutoVoIPVLAN.name: agentAutoVoIPVLAN
agentAutoVoIPVLAN.description: The VLAN to which all VoIP traffic is mapped to.

agentAutoVoIPOUIPriority.name: agentAutoVoIPOUIPriority
agentAutoVoIPOUIPriority.description: The priority to which all VoIP traffic with known OUI is mapped to.

agentAutoVoIPProtocolPriScheme.name: agentAutoVoIPProtocolPriScheme
agentAutoVoIPProtocolPriScheme.description: The priotization scheme which is used to priritize the voice data.

agentAutoVoIPProtocolTcOrRemarkValue.name: agentAutoVoIPProtocolTcOrRemarkValue
agentAutoVoIPProtocolTcOrRemarkValue.description: If 'agentAutoVoIPProtocolPriScheme' is traffic class, then the object 'agentAutoVoIPProtocolTcOrRemarkValue' is CoS Queue value to which all VoIP traffic is mapped to. if 'agentAutoVoIPProtocolPriScheme' is remark, then the object 'agentAutoVoIPProtocolTcOrRemarkValue' is 802.1p priority to which all VoIP traffic is remarked at the ingress port. This is used by Protocol based Auto VoIP

agentAutoVoIPTable.name: agentAutoVoIPTable
agentAutoVoIPTable.description: A table providing configuration of Auto VoIP Profile.

agentAutoVoIPEntry.name: agentAutoVoIPEntry
agentAutoVoIPEntry.description: Auto VoIP Profile configuration for a port.

agentAutoVoIPIntfIndex.name: agentAutoVoIPIntfIndex
agentAutoVoIPIntfIndex.description: This is a unique index for an entry in the agentAutoVoIPTable. A non-zero value indicates the ifIndex for the corresponding interface entry in the ifTable. A value of zero represents global configuration, which in turn causes all interface entries to be updated for a set operation, or reflects the most recent global setting for a get operation.

agentAutoVoIPProtocolMode.name: agentAutoVoIPProtocolMode
agentAutoVoIPProtocolMode.description: Enables / disables AutoVoIP Protocol profile on an interface.

agentAutoVoIPOUIMode.name: agentAutoVoIPOUIMode
agentAutoVoIPOUIMode.description: Enables / disables AutoVoIP OUI profile on an interface.

agentAutoVoIPProtocolPortStatus.name: agentAutoVoIPProtocolPortStatus
agentAutoVoIPProtocolPortStatus.description: AutoVoIP protocol profile operational status of an interface.

agentAutoVoIPOUIPortStatus.name: agentAutoVoIPOUIPortStatus

agentAutoVoIPOUI.description: The Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI), as defined in IEEE std 802-2001, is a 24 bit (three octets) globally unique assigned number referenced by various standards, of the information received from the remote system.

agentAutoVoIPOUIDesc.name: agentAutoVoIPOUIDesc
agentAutoVoIPOUIDesc.description: The Description of the Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI), as defined in IEEE std 802-2001(up to 32 characters)
